  "texts": [
    "In this case, the two errors have the same action on any encoded (logical) state.",
    "Thus, applying the inverse of the guessed error returns data qubits to the initial logical sate.",
    "Otherwise, if the guessed and the actual error differ by a non-trivial logical operator, error correction fails resulting in a logical error.",
    "Our numerical experiments are based on the belief propagation with an ordered statistics decoder (BP-OSD) proposed by Panteleev and Kalachev 36.",
    "The original work 36 described BP-OSD in the context of a toy noise model with memory errors only."
